&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Integrated Safeguarding Team as a Support Practitioner in the Single Point of Contact( SPOC).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a newly created post and the successful applicant will have the opportunity to further develop the scope and remit of this varied and challenging role . It will involve the provision of a triage process for contacts with the SPOC , along with responsibility for inputting and evaluation of data, so a sound understanding of the safeguarding agenda is essential, along with accurate keyboard skills and the ability to use Excel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return the successful applicant will join a multi-disciplinary team, who offer a strong culture of support and development with access to training and supervision and the opportunity to progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact Amanda Garnett, Safeguarding Senior Lead on amanda.garnett@nottshc.nhs.uk or 07917 558747&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
